WEBVTT

00:03:29.685 --> 00:03:33.192
The second reason why people at work
are attracted to each other

00:03:33.216 --> 00:03:36.172
is they may often be
similar to each other.

00:03:36.196 --> 00:03:37.944
There's two old adages:

00:03:37.948 --> 00:03:41.042
"Birds of a feather flock together."
And "Opposites attract."

00:03:41.082 --> 00:03:44.673
Well, the psychological
research suggests ...

00:03:44.673 --> 00:03:46.845
birds of a feather flock together,

00:03:46.845 --> 00:03:48.744
and we like people who are like us.

00:03:48.744 --> 00:03:49.889
Question six:

00:03:49.913 --> 00:03:51.761
My coworkers are flirting.

00:03:51.761 --> 00:03:53.604
I'm annoyed. What do I do?

00:03:53.628 --> 00:03:57.152
Some researchers argue
that for people flirting at work,

00:03:57.176 --> 00:03:59.556
flirting is good and it boosts creativity.

00:03:59.580 --> 00:04:02.514
But my own research suggests
things are different